As we are unable to fully implement the import substitution mechanism at this stage, as well as increase the self-sufficiency of the Russian market at the expense of domestic production, retaliatory sanctions will continue to carry risks of inflationary growth.
If we add to this the fiscal reasons related to the lack of confidence in the national currency, as well as the worsening prospects for economic growth, inflation could well exceed 8% by the end of this year.
Alexander Razuvaev, director of the analytical department of Alpari
In the 1990s, inflation sometimes reached 20-30% per month, and in the zero years it was also above the current level, another thing that was compensated for by rapid economic growth.
I think inflation will be 8 to 8.5 percent by the end of the year.
Plato Maguta, the asset manager of the Maguta Foundation.
