The first day of spring is marked by wet and windy conditions affecting flights at Adelaide Airport
A FREDDY spring has brought a surprise to the south of South Australia, with torrential rains and strong winds that have affected flights at Adelaide Airport.
Another 5 mm of rain fell on the city by 9 pm, following the 6.6 mm that fell on Sunday night.
The latest rain was preceded by a pair of short downpours with gusty winds, including thunderstorms that began shortly before 8 p.m. and rained nearly 4 mm in about 10 minutes.
